oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Young woman dressed up in man's suit
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Image of a woman dressed in a man's white suit, holding a cane with one hand, and the other hand in the breast pocket of her coat. "Friday - November 18 - 1911-, 26 F. St." is written on the scrapbook page.
This is the first of two houses the Crofts owned in Havana and was located at 26 F Street in Vedado. The second house was located at the corner of 19 and F Streets, Vedado.
